👋🏽 Hello, my name is Seryeong Kyun.

🌇 Business owner and founder, with a strong passion for data-driven decision-making and adept at resolving challenges through insights grounded in legal frameworks.

📚 I worked in the legal team at Halla Corporation, a major construction company in South Korea, for two years. Afterward, I served as a government official in Suwon City, South Korea. For the past six years, I have been running my own study center business.

💻 I am excited about the opportunity to apply these experiences to support cybercrime initiatives by using data-driven insights to enhance digital security and mitigate emerging threats.

🏔 In my free time, I enjoy camping.

💪 Specialties in analyzing customer-driven data from e-commerce and applying insights to actionable strategies.

+ Programming: Python, R
+ Data visualization: Tableau Software, Power BI
+ Database: SQL, Postgre SQL, MongoDB, Neo4j
+ Cloud Computing: AWS, GCP (BigQuery), Azure
